<center>This lighting example takes place an a completely dark map.
The only light is coming from the point lights scattered around the map.
Try disabling lighting on this map in the editor to see what it looks like
without lights!</center>

<center>Placed lights can emit light at a customizable
range and intensity - they can also optionally flicker.
Entities can also have lights attached directly to them,
so if you need a moving light source they are able to
emit light</center>

$values.Body:
<center>Tile Tags
Tile Tags can be applied to placed tiles, including Structures, and can
be set to play an idle and/or movement animation in association with
the player walking on top of a tile that has a tile tag assignment.
Walking on the grass will kick around a simple dirt-particle animation.</center>

<center>You may find you cannot walk on the grass... that's because
the tile tag won't allow passability unless a certain condition is met -
in this case, you are not the proper rank/level to walk on the grass, but
this could also be set to holding an item, weapon, armor, etc.
You can enforce passability limitations in this way.
</center>

<center>You may now interact with the animated entity nearby to access
a leveling dialogue menu that can reset your character's rank (i.e. level)
and add 1 to the rank value repeatadly... 
</center>
